content.description: Classic taylors eliminate! Start on big "Horn" front and center. Use smear feet and a high step/hand foot to gain the lip. all face holds are off, except the HORN!!
content.location: trailside on the path down to the tour boat. past the REI toprope spot, on the right.

content.description: Classic eliminate! start with left hand on small crimp side-pull, right hand on good  side-pull jug. Compress and stand your way up on crimps and edges. Big jug ledge on the left is off, as well as big holds around the Arete to the left.
content.location: On the unknown boulder slab side! just to the right of the big face holds.

content.description: Sit start. Basically Straight up, one of the most obvious routes.

I know this boulder has been climbed alot, and probably has a name, but I couldn't find it on the website, so I decided to make a page on it (please feel free to correct me if you know more about this boulder). A good warm up boulder with fun crimps.  There are a ton of routes to work out/make.  Add some comments and routes! PLEASE POST INFO ON THIS BOULDER IF YOU KNOW IT/THIS IS JUST A TEMPORARY PAGE THAT LACKS A PROPER NAME AND ROUTES.
